Bang for the buck, you will be in dangerous areas with hard hitting mobs where the risk is not only high but often severely dangerous. The areas we speak of are Bot lower and tower bosses, PoTactics (named and pit/arena area), Hall of Honour, CoDecay. You can easily make 5-7 PCT a kill. If we lose 1 PCT to the pet, it will be fine. On a typical cycle of CoD you will be able to easily kill 3 mobs. That is 15 PCT of an AA in 8 minutes. This ratio can easily be 1 AA an hour. The truly adventorous types will get more. <br>
There is no magic really for solo charming normal mobs. You mezz, tash, charm, haste, guard pet. With sleep you have 54 seconds to get your new mob debuffed before you cast CoD. Once you have your pet, you can move towards a mob. Again, sick pet onto mob, tash, slow, root and stand back in safety. Be aware of enrage on these mobs (and they will enrage at 10%) so you will have to back your pet off for a few seconds during enrage (if solo) because this is where the pet will lose most of their HPs. After about the 3rd mob, your pet will be very lw on HPs. If you are soloing, just zone out. No healing, no aggro and it allows you time to med up from that flurry of action.<br>
If you duo charm (with NON chanters) there is more safety for you but the technique is fairly similiar.<br>
 <p>Tripts Alot<br>
<br>
65th Charmer of<br>
Royal Norrathian Guards<br>
