<br>
the basics are simple. tash, charm, park. pull another mob with tash, root him on incoming. send the pet after the mob... slow the mob, haste your pet. after you've done it for a while you'll get a feel for certain pets that hold charm better, and what ones break charm often. its good to duo with someone who can snare.. having them pull with snare, then charming is quite an advantage since your pet wont be too fast of a runner. <br>
<br>
some basic tricks... are 1) always always always have a rune up, it will save your life more times than you'll notice. 2) always have a fast casting stun loaded, it'll make re-charming something tons easier. 3) try not to sit too often during charming, it might not be as bad where mobs only hit for 100 or so, but in the planes a double or triple for 300+, but when they break charm while you're sitting, it can get ugly if you try to stand and the hit you at the same time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
dont think that because some people are good about charming, or maybe brag about it, that it just happened overnight and bam they're doing an AA every 30 minutes. it takes a good while of practice and technique, and there's much strategy that goes into it.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
there are some pretty decent guides, might want to check the &quot;old stuff&quot; forum, not sure if they've been moved over there or what. i'll probably get bored enough soon, so i'll see if i can write up a good guide here shortly. good luck with charming =) <p>Charmroxors<br>
